                            <comment id="367342" author="adilger" created="Sun, 26 Mar 2023 23:30:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In all of the cases where &lt;tt&gt;fs_log_size()&lt;/tt&gt; is checked (&lt;tt&gt;runtests&lt;/tt&gt; included) the actual space compared was based on OST space usage.  However, it looks like &lt;tt&gt;runtests&lt;/tt&gt; was failing because &lt;tt&gt;fs_log_size()&lt;/tt&gt; was scaling the returned value based on the MDT count, and not on the OST count.  It looks like the main &quot;leakage&quot; of space on the OSTs was only due to blocks being allocated to the object directories &lt;tt&gt;O/&amp;lt;seq&amp;gt;/dN&lt;/tt&gt;, and this was very obvious when &lt;tt&gt;runtests&lt;/tt&gt; was run in isolation and failed repeatedly, but passed if it was run after other tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change &lt;tt&gt;fs_log_size()&lt;/tt&gt; to scale the &quot;slop&quot; by &lt;tt&gt;OSTCOUNT&lt;/tt&gt; rather than &lt;tt&gt;MDTCOUNT&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="367341" author="adilger" created="Sun, 26 Mar 2023 23:25:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/50419&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/50419&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
