                            <comment id="331872" author="adilger" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2022 20:18:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems unlikely that this is a straight duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12807&quot; title=&quot;runtests test 1 fails with &amp;#39;&amp;#39;Space not all freed: now 180500kB, was 180424kB.&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12807&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12807&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, since that was dealing with a difference of only 64KB, while this is 144KB difference or more.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There have been 15 similar failures in the past 4 weeks, but it goes back a long time and it could just be a slow bleed from 64KB to 144KB of space usage.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
